A vintage 1960s technical illustration showing an intricate mechanical sorting machine with brass gears, conveyor belts, and glass tubes, transforming stacks of ornate paper scrolls covered in dense symbols into neatly organized rows of index cards emerging from the other side. The machine sits on a wooden desk with warm amber lighting from a green banker's lamp. Sepia and copper tones dominate, with subtle touches of forest green. Small mechanical arms with magnifying glasses inspect each scroll before processing. Steam wisps curl from exhaust pipes. The aesthetic combines Victorian engineering diagrams with mid-century technical manual illustrations.
